 How HTML's FORM Element Works<body>
 How HTML's FORM Element Works 

The following HTML:
 
&lt;FORM ACTION=" 
http://eee.uci.edu/96b/36246/cgi-bin/formval.cgi " METHOD=POST&gt;
&lt;INPUT TYPE=HIDDEN NAME="Secret" VALUE="Quiet"&gt;
First entry: &lt;INPUT NAME="Entry1"&gt;
&lt;BR&gt;Second Entry: &lt;INPUT NAME="Entry2" VALUE="Anteater"&gt;
&lt;BR&gt;Select Color: &lt;SELECT NAME="Color"&gt;
   &lt;OPTION VALUE="Rd"&gt;Red
   &lt;OPTION VALUE="Gr"&gt;Green
   &lt;OPTION VALUE="Bl"&gt;Blue
   &lt;/SELECT&gt;
&lt;BR&gt;
&lt;INPUT TYPE=submit NAME=submit Value="Submit Information"&gt; 
&lt;INPUT TYPE=reset NAME=reset Value="Clear Form"&gt; 
&lt;/FORM&gt;
 

 Appears as follows:  

First entry:  Second Entry:  Select Color:  

 
Suggested by
 
 http://www.utoronto.ca/webdocs/HTMLdocs/NewHTML/forms.html  
  
 ICS 1C, Summer 1996 

 </body> 